HEADWORD: Neutrophile
<hw>Neu"tro*phile</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>neuter</ets> + Gr. <?/
loving.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>One of a group of leukocytes
whose granules stain only with neutral dyes; it is the chief phagocytic
leukocyte in the circulating blood, comprising from 54% to 65% of the
total number of leukocytes.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Neu"tro*phil"ic</wf>
<pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>, <wf>Neu*troph"i*lous</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>neutrosophy</ent>⟦br⟧
